"title": "4933: evening",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4933: evening",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The time between the fading of daylight and nightfall. The onset of darkness marks the end of the working day and is a time for rest and refreshment. It is an assigned time for sacrifice and an opportunity for reflection and prayer. The evening also brings dangers.</p>\n<h2>Evening marks the end of the day</h2>\n<h3>Evening and God's work of creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>The onset of darkness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:9\">PRO 7:9</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:11\">PSA 102:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps109:23\">PSA 109:23</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:4\">JER 6:4</a></p>\n<h3>Days reckoned from evening to evening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:18\">EXO 12:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:32\">LEV 23:32</a> <em>The Sabbath began at sunset on Friday.</em></p>\n<h3>Ritual uncleanness lasts until evening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:39-Lev11:40\">LEV 11:39–11:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:15\">LEV 17:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:7-Num19:8\">NUM 19:7–19:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:11\">DEU 23:11</a></p>\n<h3>Waiting on God until evening</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:6\">JOS 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:23\">JDG 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26-Judg20:27\">JDG 20:26–20:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:2-Judg21:3\">JDG 21:2–21:3</a></p>\n<h3>Mourning until evening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:12\">2SA 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>City gates shut at evening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:5\">JOS 2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:9-2Kgs7:11\">2KI 7:9–7:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:19\">NEH 13:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:2\">EZK 46:2</a></p>\n<h3>Executed criminals to be buried by evening</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:22-Deut21:23\">DEU 21:22–21:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:29\">JOS 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:26\">JOS 10:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:57-Matt27:58\">MAT 27:57–27:58</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:42-Mark15:43\">MRK 15:42–15:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:52-Luke23:54\">LUK 23:52–23:54</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:31\">JHN 19:31</a></p>\n<h2>Evening as a time for refreshment</h2>\n<h3>A time to rest from labour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:23\">PSA 104:23</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:37\">LUK 21:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:16\">JDG 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:17\">RUT 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job7:2\">JOB 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph2:7\">ZEP 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:8\">MAT 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:35-Mark4:38\">MRK 4:35–4:38</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:23\">MAT 8:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:22-Luke8:23\">LUK 8:22–8:23</a></p>\n<h3>A time to rest from travel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:9\">JDG 19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:1-Gen19:2\">GEN 19:1–19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:21\">NUM 9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:29\">LUK 24:29</a></p>\n<h3>A time to return home</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:17\">MAT 21:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:16\">GEN 30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:11\">MRK 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:19\">MRK 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:16-John6:17\">JHN 6:16–6:17</a></p>\n<h3>A time to eat</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:12\">EXO 16:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:15\">MAT 14:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:2\">JHN 13:2</a></p>\n<h3>A time for reflection and prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:63\">GEN 24:63</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:2\">PSA 141:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:23\">MAT 14:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:46\">MRK 6:46</a></p>\n<h2>Evening religious duties</h2>\n<h3>The evening sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:38-Exod29:41\">EXO 29:38–29:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:8\">NUM 28:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:40\">1CH 16:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:31\">EZR 3:31</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra18:29\">18:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:4-Ezra9:5\">EZR 9:4–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:21\">DAN 9:21</a></p>\n<h3>Lighting the lamps in the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:8\">EXO 30:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:21\">EXO 27:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:3\">LEV 24:3</a></p>\n<h3>The Passover sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:6\">EXO 12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5\">LEV 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:2-Num9:5\">NUM 9:2–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:6\">DEU 16:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:10\">JOS 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:20\">MAT 26:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:17-Mark14:18\">MRK 14:17–14:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:14\">LUK 22:14</a></p>\n<h2>Adulterous behaviour in the evening</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:15\">JOB 24:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:14-Prov7:20\">PRO 7:14–7:20</a></p>\n<h2>Other evening activities</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:16\">MAT 8:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:32\">MRK 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:40\">LUK 4:40</a> <em>People came to Jesus Christ after sunset, when the Sabbath was over.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:11\">GEN 24:11</a> <em>Water collected in the evening, the coolest time of the day</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:2\">MAT 16:2</a> <em>Red sky in the evening as a sign of fair weather</em></p>\n<h2>The dangers of the evening</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:14\">ISA 17:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:3\">ZEP 3:3</a></strong> <em>Israel's rulers are likened to wolves who prowl in the evening looking for food.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:7\">2KI 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:6\">PSA 59:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:8\">HAB 1:8</a></p>",
